<TEXT>
sen william proxmire says senate support of a 
poison pill amendment would weaken his bill to make hostile 
takeovers of corporations more difficult and says he is considering 
withdrawing the legislation from the senate floor 
the amendment which the senate refused on tuesday to set aside 
would curb the poison pills the term refers to strategies used 
by target companies to make themselves less desirable to raiders 
such as issuing additional shares of stock or incurring new debt 
the vote on the amendment which was offered by sen william 
armstrong rcolo was 5740 
proxmire dwis chairman of the banking committee temporarily 
withdrew the legislation from the floor after that vote aides said 
that would give him time to examine the support he has to oppose 
several amendments by armstrong and to assess how he should deal 
with them 
asked if he might remove the bill completely from consideration 
he told a reporter theres a possibility that would happen 
yes 
earlier the lawmakers approved another amendment limiting 
golden parachutes bonuses that are sometimes paid to corporate 
managers ousted after their companies are acquired in hostile 
takeovers 
the golden parachute amendment is aimed at payments sometimes 
amounting to tens of millions of dollars that can be made to 
executives who are fired by new corporate owners the provision 
would require such bonuses to be approved by a majority vote of 
shareholders 
there is a point at which these abuses ought to be stopped or 
at least made subject to a vote of the stockholders said 
armstrong rcolo the amendments chief sponsor shortly before 
the 981 vote 
the provision as is true for many aspects of the corporate 
takeover legislation attracted an unusual coalition of supporters 
one of the senates most liberal members sen howard metzenbaum 
dohio joined conservatives armstrong sen phil gramm rtexas 
and sen richard shelby dala in cosponsoring it 
sen william roth rdel voted against the amendment saying 
that state laws should be allowed to continue to control the 
bonuses delaware corporate home of 54 percent of the companies 
listed on the new york stock exchange has strong antitakeover 
legislation of its own 
the only senator not voting was joseph biden ddel who is 
recovering from brain surgery 
armstrong argued that his poison pill amendment which would 
require that such strategies receive stockholder approval was 
needed because poison pills diminish shareholders power proxmire 
and his allies have argued that poison pills benefit stockholders 
by driving up the price raiders must pay and that there already 
are state laws that curb abuses under the procedure 
obviously we suffered a serious loss on that amendment 
proxmire said 
proxmires bill would reduce from 10 days to five days the time 
buyers of 5 percent of companys stock have to report the 
transactions to the securities and exchange commission the shorter 
window and a prohibition on buying additional stock until the 
report is completed would make it harder for a buyer to quietly 
gain control of a company 
it would require buyers to disclose more information to the sec 
such as whether they desire to simply make an investment or gain 
control of a corporation tender offers public offers to purchase 
stock at a given price would have to remain open for 35 days 
instead of the current 20 days 
the legislation would also increase criminal penalties for 
insider trading from 100000 and five years in prison to 1 
million and 10 years of imprisonment 
proxmire and his supporters say takeovers have become such a 
distraction to american business that their threat is causing 
corporate managers to focus on them rather than on improving their 
products in addition they say companies are being dismantled and 
jobs lost because of the costs of battling wouldbe buyers even 
when the corporations successfully fend off the buyers 
</TEXT>
