rudolf nureyevs version of swan lake which 
opened the paris opera ballets threeweek season at the 
metropolitan opera is not the finest production of the wellknown 
ballet nor was tuesday nights performance the best presentation 
the two stars danced very well but didnt dazzle with 
personality laurent hilaire was the most impassive prince weve 
seen isabelle guerin rippled her arms and looked appropriately 
swanlike but did not convey the aspects of the woman she was 
before evil sorcerer rothbart changed her into a swan 
when she danced the black swan miss guerin switched on 
vitality which the ballet needed badly 
hilaire has impressive height to his jumps and beats in air the 
prince and black swan when they traded variations did build 
excitement though not as much as usual in that scene 
we recall both dancers putting more oomph into their 
performances when the company presented the same ballet here two 
years ago maybe the june 14 to 19 season in costa mesa calif 
was exhausting 
nureyev whose choreography is after the early work of 
marius petipa and lev ivanov emphasizes the men more than those 
choreographers did he has one dance for four groups of four men 
one group of which couldnt stay together on tuesday 
