firm said financial markets were reassured by the final language 
because it signaled that the coordination process that has 
stabilized the dollars value can be expected to continue 
the communique itself offers little that is new but it is a 
capstone on what has been an extraordinary amount of coordination 
among countries beginning in 1985 he said it also offers the 
promise that this coordination will continue 
to further the coordination process the summit countries did 
agree to a us proposal to adopt two commodity indexes both 
including gold to monitor whether inflationary pressures are 
building 
the index was an idea first proposed by baker last september he 
has insisted that the proposal is not a first step to returning the 
world monetary system to a gold standard 
baker told reporters that the two indexes would differ in the 
weight they gave gold also one of the indexes would include oil 
while the other would not but he refused to disclose what weight 
gold would have in each of the indexes other than to say that a 
significant weight would be attached to gold 
