<TEXT>
do muoi who has directed purges 
against corruption in vietnams ruling communist party was chosen 
today as the countrys prime minister the official radio hanoi 
said 
do muoi 71 was elected on the opening day of the national 
assembly said the broadcast monitored in bangkok he replaces 
pham hung who died in march 
a party communique meanwhile said vietnams communist party 
has decided to regularly change its leadership to improve 
efficiency and better the economy 
the communique said the party central committees fifth plenum 
decided that every time the party elects members to its upper 
echelons onethird of the seats will change hands 
do muoi is the thirdranking member of the politburo the top 
policymaking body 
little known to most vietnamese do muoi gave up the vice 
premiership last year when he became the no 2 man in the party 
secretariat where a major responsibility was directing a purge of 
inept and corrupt elements in the 18millionmember communist 
party before that the veteran revolutionary had a long list of 
key party and government jobs 
the central committee is the policyimplementing arm of the most 
powerful party organ the politburo the committee had 124 full 
members and 49 alternate members when it was elected in december 
1986 
a text of the plenum communique carried by the official 
domestic radio hanoi tuesday was obtained from a western embassy 
in bangkok the june 1420 plenum was convened to prepare for 
todays national assembly session 
a separate radio hanoi broadcast said tuesday that the assembly 
would take up the very hot issue of how to resolve the crisis 
in grain production vietnam has asked the international community 
for emergency aid to offset serious food shortages resulting from a 
series of crop failures last year 
since the party was founded in 1930 its leaders have largely 
been veterans of the revolutionary struggle against the french 
colonialists and then the americans and south vietnam lately the 
party set economic reform as its no 1 priority and says 
incompetent party members with outdated ways of thinking can no 
longer remain in powerful positions 
the plenum communique says the party will combine elderly 
cadres with young cadres avoid renovating and rejuvenating the 
contingent of cadres for the sake of formality by referring only to 
ages and academic degrees and overcome the class ideology and 
hierarchy 
party committee secretaries generally will not remain in their 
posts for more than 10 years it adds 
the communique says managers of state and business enterprises 
and leading cadres of mass organizations need not be party members 
in the past such positions have normally gone to party members 
it says competent cadres in local areas should be brought to 
centrallevel agencies and those cadres who have no ability and 
quality to perform assigned duties must be relieved of of their 
leading positions 
there has been a major purification campaign in the 18 
millionmember party including largescale purges since linh came 
to power in december 1986 
the communique said while most party members retained their 
revolutionary qualities the fighting will of quite a number of 
cadres and party members has declined and their revolutionary 
ideals have faded making them degenerate and deviant 
