<TEXT>
alan simpson of wyoming has climbed toward the 
peak of the senates republican ranks with a determined lawmaking 
style thats spiced with a rangeland wit and outspoken irreverence 
ive punched the lights out of every sacred cow in this 
city he says 
despite his blunt independence the 56yearold attorney from 
cody wyo is being mentioned as a possible running mate for 
george bush not surprisingly hes less than enthusiastic 
i just cant imagine myself in the capacity of a vice 
presidential running mate he said citing the loss of privacy 
and freedom hed have to endure it would be a very difficult 
thing for me to do 
i cant get out of a plane in detroit and have somebody hand 
me a speech and tell me what i have to say i have an aversion to 
that its almost physical he said in an interview 
simpson has been writing his own speeches since he entered the 
senate a decade ago after serving in his state legislature 
including majority leader of the wyoming house of representatives 
in 1984 after only a single sixyear term he was named by his 
gop colleagues as deputy majority leader had republican leader bob 
doles campaign for the partys presidential nomination succeeded 
simpson would have been hard to beat for the top job 
his is a distinctive presence on the senate floor 
sixfootseven stoop shouldered thin and balding he stares 
menacingly over his halfframe glasses like a vulture and surveys 
the senate floor for prey 
then he smiles and compares passing a tough bill to giving 
dry birth to a porcupine 
simpson is known as one who fights to win his arguments not 
just go for the easy compromise he arms himself by studying at 
home late into the night 
hes been critical of some of the most popular programs in 
washington including veterans benefits for noncombatants 
costofliving increases for entitlements and rural electric 
cooperatives 
he has sometimes shown impatience with colleagues even gop 
colleagues who use the senates arcane rules to make things 
difficult but his ability to soothe and work with opponents while 
maintaining his priorities has earned him respect from both parties 
simpsons credentials as a conservative are unquestioned but 
hes not aligned with the new right 
his father milward simpson was a governor and a senator his 
leap from the statehouse to washingtons most exclusive club and 
his reelection in 1984 were made with ease 
the marathon and ultimately successful effort to overhaul the 
nations immigration laws has been simpsons most noted 
accomplishment it was he said one of those porcupine bills 
simpson teamed up with rep romano mazzoli dky and spent six 
years crafting and pushing the immigration bill to final approval 
along the way the measure became known simply as 
simpsonmazzoli and it was signed into law by president reagan 
in november 1986 
along with the successes have come frustrations especially 
with the inability of washington to resist special interest 
lobbying and attack federal deficits 
hes not shy about making those feelings known and his humor 
can take an edge when hes on the attack his jokes are my sword 
and my shield he says 
simpson says his friend george bush will find many who are 
qualified to be his running mate he says whoever is chosen hes 
confident the republicans will hold the white house 
