hungarian composer bela bartok began his 
final journey home wednesday 43 years after his death as almost 
150 family and friends gathered around his american gravesite to 
bid him farewell 
bartoks remains were exhumed from westchesters ferncliff 
cemetery and he will be buried in budapest near his mother and 
wife 
as we are immensely proud to know that he was very hungarian 
we are aware that he and his lifes work belong to the whole 
world gyorgy banlaki the hungarian consul general told the 
gathering he was international he is international and we want 
to keep it that way 
on hand were bartoks sons bela jr 78 of budapest and 
peter 64 of homossassa fla they decided to move their fathers 
body during the younger sons visit to budapest last year 
i felt it was the wish of the entire hungarian nation that he 
should be there said peter bartok after the ceremony it 
became my wish too here my father is entirely alone there are 
all the people who were close to him in life he will never be 
alone 
his father had always wanted to return to hungary but died in 
1945 of leukemia at age 64 before he could go back said peter 
the sons will accompany their fathers remains throughout the 
sixcountry trip which will feature concerts and recitals 
the remains exhumed tuesday were in a new coffin and a huge 
packing crate festooned with red white and green ribbons the 
colors of the hungarian flag 
thomas simons us deputy assistant secretary of state praised 
the composer on behalf of the us government 
bartok combined in himself and his music the best of hungary 
and the best of the outside world who chose exile rather than 
acquiescence when he left hungary in 1940 on a piano concert tour 
and did not return because of world war ii simons said 
bartok was known for popularizing and chronicling hungarys folk 
music and incorporating it into his own works banlaki said the 
composers popularity was evident almost everywhere in hungary 
countless streets schools institutions bear his name there 
is hardly a locality in the whole country where something would not 
bear his name banlaki said his portrait adorns the countrys 
biggest bank note 
hungarian flutist juli zabos of ossining played two bartok 
pieces during the ceremony and a group of fans broke into song 
afterward 
after the ceremony cemetery workers removed the original grave 
marker and replaced it with a new one 
it read in hungarian and english the first resting place of 
bela bartok remains moved to farkasret cemetery budapest 
hungary following june 25 1988 
after a departure on the queen elizabeth 2 on saturday the 
remains will arrive in southampton england amid fanfare and 
concerts and a message from british prime minister margaret 
thatcher 
the ship then heads to cherbourg the sons will accompany the 
body through france germany and austria before arriving in hungary 
after a public display of the coffin bartok will be laid to 
rest july 7 in budapest 
