president reagan signed legislation wednesday 
aimed at improving rail safety in the wake of a january 1987 crash 
of amtrak and conrail trains that killed 16 people 
the legislation among other things requires the licensing and 
certification of locomotive operators and prescribes new 
requirements for the use of safetyrelated equipment on trains 
