secretary of transportation in connection with railroad 
investigations and revises federal rail safety statutes to increase 
penalties for violations 
investigators of the crash near chase md that killed 16 and 
injured 175 found that a device had been disabled on the conrail 
train that would have warned the trains operators they had passed 
a stop signal 
