brazil has reached agreement with 
international bankers on its huge foreign debt the countrys 
finance minister said 
we have concluded all points of the accord finance minister 
mailson da nobrega said tuesday brazil is satisfied with the 
agreement it is the best accord reached so far with bankers 
the agreement which gives brazil 52 billion in new loans was 
not immediately signed but a communique would be issued in new york 
and brazil within the next two days da nobrega said 
brazils 700 creditor banks must still work out the exact amount 
each would give the country however brazil is not involved in 
that part of the agreement da nobrega said 
brazils owes its creditors a total of 120 billion making it 
the largest debtor among developing countries 
finance ministry representatives and a committee representing 
the creditors have been negotiating for months on an accord that 
would satisfy all parties 
brazil is to receive 46 billion this year and 600 million 
during the first three months of 1989 the last installment is 
