order that the new york susquehanna amp western railway another 
regional rail line in the northeast assume the service of the damph 
the damph a subsidiary of guilford railroad co provides service 
over nearly 1700 miles of track in vermont new york 
pennsylvania new jersey maryland and virginia 
in cooperstown ny david soule executive vice president of 
delaware amp otsego corp parent of the new york susquehanna amp 
western said the railroad would take over the damph operations 
whenever it officially stops operations 
at that time we are all set to begin operating on damph 
tracks he said 
